  section#textbox-object
    h2 The Textbox Object
    p.
      The Textbox Object is similar to the Box object except that it is used for inline text only,
      such as labels or badges.
      It is usually instantiated by a #[code small] element, but that depends on context.
      Add class #[code .o-Inline] if necessary.
    figure
      p
        | The following is a Textbox: 
        span.a-bc-shadelight.o-Textbox here I am!
        |  Textboxes are inline text only.
      h3 Example h3 #[small.a-bc-shadelight.o-Textbox Textbox]
      pre.
        &lt;p&gt;... Textbox: &lt;small class="#[u o-Textbox]"&gt;here I am!&lt;/small&gt; ... &lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;Example h3 &lt;small class="#[u o-Textbox]"&gt;Textbox&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
